The paper discusses the Mathematical Theory of Evidence (MTE) and its relationship with frequencies, which are important in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses how to interpret data and generate random samples, which are topics related to statistics and information theory, making cs.SI and cs.IT likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with modeling destructive processes, which could fall under the category of data science, making cs.DS a possible sub-category.
